('408a18d4-c8e7-4437-9493-8109f64cc80b', 'Banana Milk Shake', null, 'White wine glass', false, 'Blend very well, preferably in a household mixer. Serve in a wine glass, garnish with whipped cream and a piece of banana.'),
('40c2972c-8760-4e8e-890a-2c05b3bf3e22', 'Banana Strawberry Shake', null, 'Highball Glass', false, 'Blend all together in a blender until smooth.'),
('630c3136-2d66-4605-bb4e-500c680e6b54', 'Banana Strawberry Shake Daiquiri', null, 'Cocktail Glass', false, 'Blend all together in a blender until smooth.'),
('e1e0ebb4-04ee-4c25-b9fc-92a533ece88a', 'Cranberry Punch', null, 'Punch Bowl', false, 'Combine first four ingredients. Stir until sugar is dissolved, chill. Then add ginger ale just before serving. Add ice ring to keep punch cold.'),
('889bff25-90df-4e02-8563-c344c8391538', 'Cranberry Cordial', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Place the chopped cranberries in a 2 liter jar that has a tight-fitting lid. Add the sugar and rum. Adjust the lid securely and place the jar in a cool, dark place. Invert the jar and shake it every day for six weeks. Strain the cordial into bottles and seal with corks.'),
('4838365a-abba-4c91-b60c-d13c70e37679', 'Absolutely Cranberry Smash', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Stir ingredients together. Serve over ice.'),
('19e81fe4-81f3-4ee5-9b79-f4faaedcec8a', 'San Francisco', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Take a tall glass and put in a few ice cubes, fill the vodka over it and fill with juice then the "creme", to end fill in the grenadine but very carefully at the side of the glass so it will lay down in the bottom. garnish with orange and strawberry.'),
('ebd88ea3-dcba-4552-b1a4-95ab47cbe43c', 'Apple Grande', null, 'Punch Bowl', true, 'Chill both ingredients!! Mix in a tumbler and enjoy!'),
('c125203d-af0b-49c7-a9f1-157f77fe52aa', 'Monkey Gland', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Shake well over ice cubes in a shaker, strain into a chilled cocktail glass.'),
('ce0103c0-0e41-4541-adab-3ab2adade2a8', 'Brandy Cobbler', null, 'Old-fashioned glass', true, 'In an old-fashioned glass, dissolve the sugar in the club soda. Add crushed ice until the glass is almost full. Add the brandy. Stir well. Garnish with the cherry and the orange and lemon slices.'),
('cb18103c-d5b2-4aa2-894d-b22ed7012031', 'Flander''s Flake-Out', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Bang ''em both in.'),
('df8a6d98-0536-4a62-af8b-1353255add1e', 'Japanese Fizz', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Shake all ingredients (except carbonated water) with ice and strain into a highball glass over two ice cubes. Fill with carbonated water, stir, and serve.'),
('d3e67f0b-478c-43ce-8888-8667443f236f', 'Orange Oasis', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Shake brandy, gin, and orange juice with ice and strain into a highball glass over ice cubes. Fill with ginger ale, stir, and serve.'),
('90e0f403-2f6c-4d0f-9793-31e05a282c6c', 'Mango Mojito', null, 'Jar', true, 'Squeeze the juice from 1½ limes and blend with the mango to give a smooth purée.
Cut the rest of the limes into quarters, and then cut each wedge in half again. Put 2 pieces of lime in a highball glass for each person and add 1 teaspoon of caster sugar and 5-6 mint leaves to each glass. Squish everything together with a muddler or the end of a rolling pin to release all the flavours from the lime and mint.
Divide the mango purée between the glasses and add 30ml white rum and a handful of crushed ice to each one, stirring well to mix everything together. Top up with soda water to serve and garnish with extra mint, if you like.'),
('380ee322-0b25-4dc7-bc07-8de76892b752', 'Lassi - Mango', null, 'Highball glass', false, 'Put it all in a blender and pour over crushed ice. You can also use other fruits like strawberries and bananas.'),
('669d7bcf-246b-4c19-9827-f082e59b83d4', 'Sweet Sangria', null, 'Pitcher', true, 'Dissolve the sugar in hot water and cool. Peel the citrus fruits and break into wedges. Mix the wine, sugar syrup, fruit, and Fresca in a pitcher and put in the fridge for a few hours. Serve in tall glasses with a straw.'),
('2af18514-cbf2-4f66-8169-a61f1bbec8ee', 'Orange Push-up', null, 'Hurricane glass', true, 'Combine liquors in a blender. Add a half scoop of ice and blend. Garnish with an orange and cherry flag. So good it will melt in your mouth!!!'),
('1c50f024-89ca-4331-bc36-44e719b0c8bb', 'Angelica Liqueur', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Combine all herbs, nuts and spices with vodka in a 1 quart or larger aging container. Cap tightly and shake daily for 2 weeks. Strain through a fine muslin cloth or coffee filter, discarding solids. Clean out aging container. Place liquid back in container. Place sugar and water in saucepan and stir to combine over medium heat. When sugar is completely dissolved, set aside and let cool. When cool combine with food coloring and add to liqueur liquid. Cap and allow to age and mellow in a cool, dark place for one month.'),
('39c4c38b-c26e-49c9-81f6-0d04385f924c', 'Harvey Wallbanger', null, 'Collins glass', true, 'Stir the vodka and orange juice with ice in the glass, then float the Galliano on top. Garnish and serve.'),
('0c6f9246-8e36-4d08-b111-e649fe059a76', 'Shanghai Cocktail', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Shake all ingredients with ice, strain into a cocktail glass, and serve.'),
('4c6c38e4-1e31-4e42-875c-62dc13d1d448', 'Auburn Headbanger', null, 'Shot glass', true, 'Mix in spread glass over ice. Strain and pour in shot glass. Sit down before shotting. ENJOY!!'),
('23972627-e9ce-4c1f-82a8-4c1a6a8a7aa3', 'White Wine Sangria', null, 'Pitcher', true, 'Chop the Lemon, Lime and other fruits into large chunks. Fill the Pitcher with the white wine and mix in the Apple Brandy. Top to taste with soda water.'),
('d0ea68c7-6fa8-4f64-b3ab-02cb334c3711', 'The Strange Weaver', null, 'Collins glass', true, 'Mix ingredients slowly in a glass with ice, garnish with orange slice'),
('01b172f8-3d88-4405-8d47-5d74b0d876c8', 'Orange Rosemary Collins', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Add the spirits to the bottom of the glass and top equally with the mixer drinks. Garnish with orange slices inside the glass as well as some rosemary on top.'),
('44690239-cfb4-4922-9b54-637c0afc48ce', 'Caribbean Orange Liqueur', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Pare very thinly the bright-colored rind from the oranges (no white). Blot the peel on paper towels to remove any excess oil. Put peel in a 4 cup screw-top jar. Add 2 cups vodka. Close jar. Store in a cool, dark place for 2 days or until the vodka has absorbed the flavor. Remove peel and add remaining vodka. Close jar and add remaining cup of vodka. Close the jar and store in a cool dark place at least 1 month to age.'),
('60dd9176-fd52-4822-9ac7-0a6e75620cb2', 'Orange Scented Hot Chocolate', null, 'Coffee mug', false, 'Combine all ingredients in heavy medium saucepan. Stir over low heat until chocolate melts. Increase heat and bring just to a boil, stirring often. Remove from heat and whisk untily frothy. Return to heat and bring to boil again. Remove from heat, whisk until frothy. Repeat heating and whisking once again. Discard orange peel. (Can be prepared 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature. Before serving, bring just to boil, remove from heat and whisk until frothy.) Pour hot chocolate into coffee mugs. Makes 2 servings.'),
('f6f3d039-7fff-4a3c-9cd8-2cefbc9bae05', 'Spanish chocolate', null, 'Coffee mug', false, 'Stir the milk with the chocolate and the cinnamon over low heat until the chocolate dissolves. Add the eggs and beat the mixture until it becomes thick, taking care not to boil. Serve in coffee mug.'),
('1d3c8684-b950-4cd8-89a2-9340f38fe3a1', 'Jack''s Vanilla Coke', null, 'Old-fashioned glass', true, 'After pouring in your ingredients, and adding 3-5 ice cubes, according to taste. Stir the drink with a stirrer to get the Vanilla off the bottom.'),
('e10de3c5-e183-434e-bd36-77b5146110c1', 'Spritz Veneziano', null, 'Wine Glass', true, 'Build into glass over ice, garnish and serve.'),
