('9daf79f9-72f7-4e28-8fca-e6690b4c5c9c', 'Cuba Libre', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Build all ingredients in a Collins glass filled with ice. Garnish with lime wedge.'),
('fa7701ee-044b-41bf-8bac-fcded1ab5bb9', 'Cuba Libra', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Fill tall glass with ice cubes. Add rum. Rub cut edge of lime on rim of glass then squeeze juice into glass. Fill with Coca-Cola. Garnish with lime slice. Enjoy!'),
('6d98029d-abe0-455a-abcf-7f331edd7859', 'Irish Curdling Cow', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Pour Irish Cream, Vodka, and Bourbon in a glass. Add some ice and mix in the orange juice.'),
('d03c0ec3-5f15-41da-8828-04df73bf3069', 'Diesel', null, 'Pint glass', true, 'Pour the lager first then add the blackcurrant cordial. Top up with the cider. The colour sholud be very dark approaching the colour of Guiness.'),
('a362289b-f7cd-493e-a48f-9b194ce55545', 'Radler', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Pour beer into large mug, slowly add the 7-up (or Sprite).'),
('eda2fa98-a519-4207-a4ae-d0d3a17690fd', 'Snowday', null, 'Collins glass', true, 'Stir all ingredients with ice. Strain into a chilled rocks glass over fresh ice. Express orange peel over drink and garnish.'),
('f93f00d2-1c0b-45be-9f44-98f2aa6b0503', 'Limeade', null, 'Highball glass', false, 'In a large glass, put the lime juice and sugar, and stir well. Add cold seltzer water to fill. Put the lime peels in the glass. Drink. Repeat until limes or soda run out.'),
('07095766-8b3b-4da5-a795-2d53d8e6d50a', 'Addison', null, 'Martini Glass', true, 'Shake together all the ingredients and strain into a cold glass.'),
('7d6c0c74-f259-4380-9ff3-3b135b6fb31f', 'Old Pal', null, 'Nick and Nora Glass', true, 'Chill cocktail glass. Add ingredients to a mixing glass, and fill 2/3 full with ice. Stir about 20 seconds. Empty cocktail glass and strain into the glass. Garnish with a twist of lemon peel.'),
('6517f8ae-fd68-4969-95a9-1f301e386c03', 'Big Red', null, 'Shot glass', true, 'Pour ingredients into 1 ounce shot glass'),
('aa1b8c48-378e-41bf-87e3-2cbb4d204eda', 'Daiquiri', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Pour all ingredients into shaker with ice cubes. Shake well. Strain in chilled cocktail glass.'),
('95eab254-5426-4318-9dc4-e28b51760ad6', 'Paradise', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Shake together over ice. Strain into cocktail glass and serve chilled.'),
('4eb0d8c0-1d29-44fd-8524-79ab22ad0cbc', 'Bluebird', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'In a mixing glass half-filled with crushed ice, combine the gin, triple sec, Curacao, and bitters. Stir well. Strain into a cocktail glass and garnish with the lemon twist and the cherry.'),
('7d1c626e-1880-4eee-bacd-f3c04991218d', 'Salty Dog', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Pour all ingredients over ice cubes in a highball glass. Stir well and serve. (Vodka may be substituted for gin, if preferred.)'),
('f3cfe3f0-0404-4cb2-b18e-1bdc61a75e3a', 'Addington', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Mix both the vermouth''s in a shaker and strain into a cold glass. Top up with a squirt of Soda Water.'),
('fff36ab9-0b3a-47ff-83c4-8ad35bafe7ae', 'Rum Toddy', null, 'Old-fashioned glass', true, 'Dissolve powdered sugar in water in an old-fashioned glass. Add rum and one ice cube and stir. Add the twist of lemon peel and serve.'),
('8f414af6-6ebc-4710-9bc3-1a1ee0cada70', 'Jam Donut', null, 'Shot glass', true, 'Coat the rim of a shot glass with sugar using sugar syrup to stick. Add the Chambord raspberry liqueur to the shot glass, and carefully layer the Baileys Irish Cream on top. Serve.'),
('c02273b2-5119-4d87-b736-87bc3ee21934', 'Iced Coffee', null, 'Coffee mug', false, 'Mix together until coffee and sugar is dissolved. Add milk. Shake well. Using a blender or milk shake maker produces a very foamy drink. Serve in coffee mug.'),
('f4a1f332-8a8e-467e-a438-acf7a9a0d7da', 'Iced Coffee Fillip', null, 'Coffee mug', true, 'Mix together in a coffee mug and chill before serving.'),
('17eb7b46-5e7d-4424-8aba-2e79476f0b91', 'Old Fashioned', null, 'Old-fashioned glass', true, 'Place sugar cube in old fashioned glass and saturate with bitters, add a dash of plain water. Muddle until dissolved.
Fill the glass with ice cubes and add whiskey.

Garnish with orange twist, and a cocktail cherry.'),
('d00415cf-55a0-4dc4-94a9-5fe966e25cdd', 'Highland Fling Cocktail', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Stir all ingredients (except olive) with ice and strain into a cocktail glass. Add the olive and serve.'),
('cb13d50f-70b4-43d1-a586-ce4aae946668', 'Bruised Heart', null, 'Shot glass', true, 'Pour all ingredients in a mixing tin over ice, stir, and strain into shot glass'),
('bb32429f-83e3-46b3-aba7-3f8116b6a48a', 'Almond Joy', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Shake all ingredients with ice, strain into a cocktail glass, and serve.'),
('5db8d80d-c98b-429b-87da-c8723c78743e', 'Scottish Highland Liqueur', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Combine all ingreds in aging container. Cover tightly and shake gently several times during the first 24 hrs. After 24 hrs, remove the lemon zest. Cover again and let stand in a cool, dark place for 2 weeks, shaking gently every other day. Strain through a wire sieve to remove the angelica root and fennel. Return to aging container, cover and let stand undisturbed in a cool dark place for 6 months. Siphon or pour clear liqueur into a sterile bottle. The cloudy dregs may be saved for cooking.'),
('9becf673-9b25-4869-a7b3-6ab90f1928ef', 'Salted Toffee Martini', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Add ice, toffee gin, chocolate liqueur and Amaretto to a cocktail shaker and shake vigorously.
Pour the chocolate syrup into a saucer and dip the top of a martini glass into the sauce. Grate some of the Willie''s sea salt chocolate into another saucer and dip the coated glass, so the flakes stick to the sauce, creating a chocolate rim!
Pour the contents of the shaker into your chocolatey glass and sprinkle with more grated chocolate - enjoy!'),
('155a2e99-dd2e-46e5-8473-f5cb58b4a1a7', 'Brigadier', null, 'Coupe Glass', true, 'Mix ingredients in a warmed mug and stir.'),
('e931fe81-6f87-475a-87bf-1db9593287ba', 'Dirty Nipple', null, 'Shot glass', true, 'This is a layered shot - the Bailey''s must be on top'),
('2f232c2d-2fd6-406f-a74e-65a74f36998f', 'Dirty Martini', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Pour the vodka, dry vermouth and olive brine into a cocktail shaker with a handful of ice and shake well.
Rub the rim of a martini glass with the wedge of lemon.
Strain the contents of the cocktail shaker into the glass and add the olive.
A dirty Martini contains a splash of olive brine or olive juice and is typically garnished with an olive.'),
('4ee569fd-1a35-4c27-b300-4054039ecc45', 'Swedish Coffee', null, 'Coffee Mug', true, 'Pour the coffee in an ordinary coffee cup. Add the aquavit. Add sugar by taste. Stir and have a nice evening (morning)'),
('255c0da0-43cd-4395-8bf6-19b9a94d8477', 'Bleeding Surgeon', null, 'Collins glass', true, 'Pour Shot of Rum over slice of orange. Fill the remaining space in glass half way full of surge or similar drink. Finish off glass with cranberry juice. Be carefull, warm surge may foam over the glass.'),
('bd238b4b-052b-4a36-8ef3-8b02a1d5049c', 'Autumn Garibaldi', null, 'Cordial glass', true, 'Pour all ingredients into a glass over ice and stir with a bar spoon. Garnish with some orange slices.'),
('2a58600e-b7d8-40c1-98d0-5f933cfb692a', 'Garibaldi Negroni', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Mix together in a shaker and garnish with a simple orange slice. Fill your vitamin C and cocktail fix at the same time!'),
('1d0eed4d-e720-413a-9400-2d9df0f93781', 'Gideon''s Green Dinosaur', null, 'Collins glass', true, 'Add all ingredients in collins glass with ice and stir.'),
('545d8334-6f01-4bbd-9ccb-5034a104e2eb', 'Lemouroudji', null, 'Highball Glass', false, 'Juice the lemons. Peel and grate the ginger. Place the grated ginger and a liberal dash of the cayenne pepper into a piece of cheesecloth, and tie it into a knot. Let soak in the water. After 15 minutes or so, add the sugar, and the lemon juice. Chill, and serve.'),
('09180762-192c-4a26-b600-1320f939b01a', 'Long vodka', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Shake a tall glass with ice cubes and Angostura, coating the inside of the glass. Por the vodka onto this, add 1 slice of lime and squeeze juice out of remainder, mix with tonic, stir and voila you have a Long Vodka'),
('7bcbe88c-9aaa-44e3-ae05-20a862533d26', 'Vodka Fizz', null, 'White wine glass', true, 'Blend all ingredients, save nutmeg. Pour into large white wine glass and sprinkle nutmeg on top.'),
('d6104145-ab86-4028-ae6c-a1e54369c599', 'Vodka Slime', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Fill glass with ice. Add vodka, 7-up then finish with the lime juice.'),
('f453bbbd-bdbd-455d-b8b8-f213fa3f4629', 'Vodka Lemon', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'The vodka lemon is prepared directly in a highball glass or in a large tumbler: put 6-7 ice cubes in the glass, pour the vodka, lemonade and mix with a bar spoon. Finally decorate with a slice of lemon and, if you prefer, add a few mint leaves. Your vodka lemon is ready to be served.'),
('1352f403-ba9b-4119-8621-de5e0a3dba89', 'Vodka Tonic', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Wash and cut 1 wedge and 1 slice of lime or lemon.
Fill a tumbler with fresh ice.
Pour the desired dose of vodka and top up with the tonic.
Squeeze the lime wedge into the glass and decorate with the slice.
That''s all, very simple: it''s just the recipe for happiness!'),
('d45619eb-1431-4785-a2e0-de4f4b42b323', 'Coffee-Vodka', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Boil water and sugar until dissolved. Turn off heat. Slowly add dry instant coffee and continue stirring. Add a chopped vanilla bean to the vodka, then combine the cooled sugar syrup and coffee solution with the vodka. Cover tightly and shake vigorously each day for 3 weeks. Strain and filter. Its also best to let the sugar mixture cool completely so the vodka won''t evaporate when its added. If you like a smoother feel to the liqueur you can add about 1 teaspoon of glycerine to the finished product.'),
('e29a5573-5513-40d7-a8fb-081fae63171e', 'Vodka Martini', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Shake the vodka and vermouth together with a number of ice cubes, strain into a cocktail glass, add the olive and serve.'),
('5609f680-c9d1-4d4a-9066-c8012fc6b8ae', 'Vodka Russian', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Mix it as a ordinary drink .'),
('5c33bbb7-1920-4394-9195-a06fc55a10e4', 'Flaming Dr. Pepper', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Add Amaretto, Bacardi, and vodka. Mix in the Dr. Pepper and beer'),
('0d7424da-f87a-4735-bd23-e7a9cb7d942b', 'Broadside', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Half fill the glass with ice cubes. Crush the wormwood and add to ice. Pour rum, scotch and butters, then serve!'),
('0da4c638-f4ef-4a00-a3d2-e175bc99d647', 'Oreo Mudslide', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Blend Vodka, Kahlua, Bailey''s, ice-cream and the Oreo well in a blender. Pour into a large frosted glass. Garnish with whipped cream and a cherry.'),
('53fb913b-df19-47a6-a487-01f5d931e8a7', 'A midsummernight dream', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Mix the strawberrys in a blender Pour it together with the vodka,kirch and strawberry liquer over ice in a shaker. Shake well and pour in a highballglass. Fill up with the Russchian water'),
('b193ed05-9728-4569-9c31-987f8fa3741d', 'Rum Old-fashioned', null, 'Old-fashioned glass', true, 'Stir powdered sugar, water, and bitters in an old-fashioned glass. When sugar has dissolved add ice cubes and light rum. Add the twist of lime peel, float 151 proof rum on top, and serve.'),
('b88d6680-5c95-4c3c-9f99-984876d36e09', 'Mulled Wine', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Simmer 3 cups water with, sugar, cloves, cinnamon sticks, and lemon peel in a stainless steel pot for 10 minutes. Add wine heat to a "coffee temperature" (DO NOT BOIL) then add the brandy.'),
('c6d7bb71-d025-480b-8708-e8c68843b5ea', 'Red Snapper', null, 'Old-fashioned glass', true, 'One shot each, shake n shoot'),
('58e1e35d-2967-47e9-9336-e05b6214fab7', 'Kool-Aid Shot', null, 'Old-fashioned glass', true, 'Pour into a large glass with ice and stir. Add a little cranberry juice to taste.'),
('7764e28f-c2db-4ccd-8623-190921f7c9e0', 'Darkwood Sling', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'There are many good cherry liqueurs you can use, but I prefere Heering. Add one share of the liqueur. Then you add one share of Soda. For a sour sling use Tonic (most people prefer the drink without Tonic). Afterwards you fill the glass with Orange Juice and ice cubes.'),
('db53bb66-475b-444f-9ab6-9ecd311dd775', 'Freddy Kruger', null, 'Shot glass', true, 'make it an ample size shot!!'),
('ce40e69a-b227-4c1b-b632-858fdc24fb7b', 'Tuxedo Cocktail', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Stir all ingredients with ice and strain into a cocktail glass. Garnish with a cherry and a twist of lemon zest.'),
('1ee381fe-b1f7-4c3b-8977-8063a90ab31f', 'Sea breeze', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Build all ingredients in a highball glass filled with ice. Garnish with lime wedge.'),
('e1aafe0b-2355-4b31-8fd2-0a1bd535a87d', 'Sweet Tooth', null, 'Highball Glass', true, 'Put 2 shots Godiva Liquour into a glass, add as much or as little milk as you would like.'),
('6cf51da8-cdab-4022-bbbb-3be6d2710001', 'Thai Coffee', null, 'Highball glass', false, 'Place the coffee and spices in the filter cone of your coffee maker. Brew coffee as usual, let it cool. In a tall glass, dissolve 1 or 2 teaspoons of sugar in an ounce of the coffee (it''s easier to dissolve than if you put it right over ice). Add 5-6 ice cubes and pour coffee to within about 1 inch of the top of the glass. Rest a spoon on top of the coffee and slowly pour whipping cream into the spoon. This will make the cream float on top of the coffee rather than dispersing into it right away.'),
('b4cf9268-54f6-47d4-adba-b73733c2c94f', 'Kioki Coffee', null, 'Coffee mug', true, 'Stir. Add whipped cream to the top.'),
('8616b4e2-a50d-4894-8089-f9b84a179321', 'Green Goblin', null, 'Pint glass', true, 'Cider First, Lager then Curacao'),
('b5fcc2b8-715c-412c-938f-34cd29d6717c', 'Irish Coffee', null, 'Irish coffee cup', true, 'Heat the coffee, whiskey and sugar; do not boil. Pour into glass and top with cream; serve hot.'),
('a50175a5-ad86-4fe8-a452-fe0412a8cdf2', 'Talos Coffee', null, 'Brandy snifter', true, 'Add your GM and then add your coffee.'),
('96e7d9e5-3d00-49f9-a8cc-97f5c86a0df5', 'Tennesee Mud', null, 'Coffee Mug', true, 'Mix Coffee, Jack Daniels and Amaretto. Add Cream on top.'),
('b72b9250-fd88-4ece-9ce6-685ed22bf5f0', 'Lassi - Sweet', null, 'Highball glass', false, 'Put all ingredients into a blender and blend until nice and frothy. Serve chilled.'),
('dda65375-f553-4e93-aa95-57658a904733', 'Spiking coffee', null, 'Coffee mug', false, 'Incidentally, a pinch of cinnamon is indeed a nice addition to coffee but true heaven is a cardamom seed. Of course, you serve it in a coffee mug.'),
('e84b217f-a075-4b23-bf96-f64324dc68dd', 'Coffee Liqueur', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Combine coffee, sugar and water. Simmer 1 hour and let cool. Add vanilla and vodka. Age in sealed jar 2 to 3 weeks.'),
('0221fe98-51a9-4715-b978-fcd07c993a43', 'Lone Tree Cooler', null, 'Collins glass', true, 'Stir powdered sugar and 2 oz. carbonated water in a collins glass. Fill glass with ice, add gin and vermouth, and stir. Fill with carbonated water and stir again. Add the twist of lemon peel and the orange spiral so that the end dangles over rim of glass.'),
('d1e35df9-1818-4ae1-b997-5c5c0e55a682', 'Lone Tree Cocktail', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Stir ingredients with ice, strain into a cocktail glass, and serve.'),
('5ebea1f7-7ab7-46fd-a5a4-89d37cd18a04', 'Espresso Rumtini', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Mix together in a cocktail glass. Garnish with some choclate powder and coffee beans'),
('190f5056-6657-4a6d-8e19-6ecbdae50e1c', 'Egg Nog #4', null, 'Punch bowl', false, 'In a small mixer bowl beat egg yolks till blended. Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating at high speed till thick and lemon colored. Stir in milk, stir in rum, bourbon, vanilla, and salt. Chill thoroughly. Whip cream. Wash beaters well. In a large mixer bowl beat egg whites till soft peaks form. Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar, beating to stiff peaks. Fold yolk mixture and whipped cream into egg whites. Serve immediately. Sprinkle nutmeg over each serving. Serve in a punch bowl or another big bowl. NOTE: For a nonalcoholic eggnog, prepare Eggnog as above, except omit the bourbon and rum and increase the milk to 3 cups.'),
('6cb94b5a-5afe-4de3-ae89-6adca8c811e0', 'Sherry Eggnog', null, 'Collins glass', true, 'Shake sherry, powdered sugar, and egg with ice and strain into a collins glass. Fill with milk and stir. Sprinkle nutmeg on top and serve.'),
('33da4395-439e-4548-835c-b5d97783b3f0', 'Egg Nog - Healthy', null, 'Collins Glass', false, 'Whip egg substitute and sugar together, combine with the two kinds of milk, vanilla, and rum. Mix well. Chill over night. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Makes 6 servings.'),
('1209b001-ed6b-41a3-87ab-b3a6c29ee776', 'Pegu Club', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Shake, strain, up, cocktail glass'),
('6fd27a2a-82f6-4b3d-a35d-9ca897da9b3a', 'Vesper', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Shake over ice until well chilled, then strain into a deep goblet and garnish with a thin slice of lemon peel.'),
('36e42cc8-1832-4372-a526-e298445dc3cc', 'Vesuvio', null, 'Old-fashioned glass', true, 'Shake all ingredients with ice, strain into an old-fashioned glass over ice cubes, and serve.'),
('b96a98fe-de7e-444e-86ed-adedac3d09b2', 'Mauresque', null, 'Collins glass', true, '1 - Pour the Ricard (or pastis)
2 - Pour the orgeat syrup
3 - Finally pour the water and add ice cubes at your convenience.

Add the ice cubes at the end, otherwise the syrup and pastis do not mix well.'),
('295fc80b-c41c-4625-966c-589b8633795a', 'Allies Cocktail', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Stir all ingredients with ice, strain contents into a cocktail glass, and serve.'),
('efe66a60-7ada-4cc4-8131-b05543980c7a', 'Espresso Martini', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Pour ingredients into shaker filled with ice, shake vigorously, and strain into chilled martini glass'),
('bba165c9-3ee9-4c48-9616-8985547b8c8a', 'Texas Rattlesnake', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Mix all ingredients and Shake well. Sweet at first, with a BITE at the end...'),
('e7ec07be-9dcf-4300-a939-d9093c05df47', 'Absolut Stress #2', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Mix well. Garnish with Orange and Cherry. Enjoy'),
('3f622aab-b1ae-4435-90b6-90baa17c51c4', 'Black Forest Shake', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'In a blender put ice cubes, chocolate syrup, cherry brandy, vodka, and milk. Blend very well.'),
('8163ecf4-5828-4302-8e8d-6f73fbfcf934', 'Gimlet', null, 'Martini Glass', true, 'Add all the ingredients to a shaker and fill with ice.

Shake, and strain into a chilled cocktail glass or an Old Fashioned glass filled with fresh ice.

Garnish with a lime wheel.'),
('a824c9b3-04b3-4c13-90d4-2683c4bc57bc', 'Amaretto Tea', null, 'Pousse cafe glass', true, 'Pour hot tea into a pousse-cafe glass, using a spoon in glass to prevent cracking. Add amaretto, but do not stir. Top with chilled whipped cream and serve.'),
('8cbd8b75-a7d6-4d2d-94e4-ad0c98754f8f', 'Amaretto Mist', null, 'Old-fashioned glass', true, 'Pour amaretto in an old-fashioned glass over crushed ice. Add the wedge of lime and serve. (A wedge of lemon may be substituted for lime, if preferred.)'),
('6d5fc9c5-8fcc-4e3d-8f74-79a9e47e57a8', 'Amaretto Rose', null, 'Collins glass', true, 'Pour amaretto and lime juice over ice in a collins glass. Fill with club soda and serve.'),
('6cbd0c1c-1073-4a05-aac4-ae3b56ee9571', 'Amaretto Sour', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Shake and strain. Garnish with a cherry and an orange slice.'),
('1d11fad8-fab3-4999-b0b1-2a6ad06d7ee0', 'Amaretto fizz', null, 'Collins glass', true, 'Mix Amaretto, orange juice and sparkling wine in a jug. Add a strip orange zest to each glass, if you like.'),
('f35b4c32-f8b6-4534-8ce0-ade106e382ac', 'Amaretto Shake', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend at high speed until smooth. Serve in chilled glass garnished with bittersweet chocolate shavings.'),
('1e3195bf-8eb1-48b0-a8b1-44581f4ad525', 'Amaretto Sunset', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Shake ingredients in bartender''s mixer quickly, just 5 shakes. Strain out ice, serve in glass immediately with a slice of orange.'),
('66e08e43-38d2-4ed5-9394-97270d5c4c11', 'Amaretto Stinger', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Shake ingredients well with cracked ice, strain into a cocktail glass, and serve.'),
('54ea2df2-2aca-4bc4-9b9a-4dd2acf9523d', 'Amaretto Liqueur', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Combine sugar and 3/4 cup water in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and simmer until all sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and cool. In an aging container, combine apricot halves, almond extract, grain alcohol with 1/2 cup water, and brandy. Stir in cooled sugar syrup mixture. Cap and let age for 2 days. Remove apricot halves. (Save apricot halves, can be used for cooking). Add food coloring and glycerine. Stir, recap and continue aging for 1 to 2 months. Re-bottle as desired. Liqueur is ready to serve but will continue to improve with additional aging.'),
('b42d71ed-1f7b-4cf3-a77b-ca854426054d', 'Amaretto Sunrise', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Mix together the amaretto and orange juice. Pour into glass and then add the grenadine untill you see the sunrise.'),
('ced0d435-302c-4e25-b40f-b1b2d79f1468', 'Amaretto Stone Sour', null, 'Collins Glass', true, 'Shake and Serve over ice'),
('6e1a518c-8916-4d71-be36-a10210253d67', 'Amaretto Sweet & Sour', null, 'Margarita/Coupette glass', true, 'Fill the blender with 3/4 ice. Add sweet & sour mix to the top of the ice. Add about 1" of pineapple juice, 1/2" of melon liqeur, and 1/2 to 1/4" of amaretto. Then blend the mix until it is of margaritta consistency or thinner.'),
('1c4e55ef-4122-45b2-bee0-3b395523e289', 'Frosé', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Step 1
Pour rosé into a 13x9" pan and freeze until almost solid (it won''t completely solidify due to the alcohol), at least 6 hours.

Step 2
Meanwhile, bring sugar and ½ cup water to a boil in a medium saucepan; cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves, about 3 minutes. Add strawberries, remove from heat, and let sit 30 minutes to infuse syrup with strawberry flavor. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve into a small bowl (do not press on solids); cover and chill until cold, about 30 minutes.

Step 3
Scrape rosé into a blender. Add lemon juice, 3½ ounces strawberry syrup, and 1 cup crushed ice and purée until smooth. Transfer blender jar to freezer and freeze until frosé is thickened (aim for milkshake consistency), 25–35 minutes.

Step 4
Blend again until frosé is slushy. Divide among glasses.

Step 5
Do Ahead: Rosé can be frozen 1 week ahead.'),
('64f02240-07d5-4bf3-a531-e722e3f60cfe', 'Frappé', null, 'Highball Glass', false, 'Mix together. Blend at highest blender speed for about 1 minute. Pour into a glass and drink with a straw. Notes: This works best if everything is cold (if you make fresh coffee, mix it with the milk and let it sit in the fridge for 1/2 hour. If it is not frothy, add more milk, or even just some more milk powder. The froth gradually turns to liquid at the bottom of the glass, so you will find that you can sit and drink this for about 1/2 hour, with more iced coffee continually appearing at the bottom. Very refreshing.'),
('61c532ec-20a4-4a99-8a0a-af31a9d3c123', 'Gin Fizz', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'Shake all ingredients with ice cubes, except soda water. Pour into glass. Top with soda water.'),
('2570c9bd-0380-4098-90c3-64283d80e1a6', 'Downshift', null, 'Hurricane glass', true, 'Start with the Sprite. Next comes the tequila. After that, add the Minute Maid Fruit Punch, then float the 151. Rocks optional.'),
('c7fdc5fe-e603-4840-8ba0-704184f6471e', 'Dragonfly', null, 'Highball glass', true, 'In a highball glass almost filled with ice cubes, combine the gin and ginger ale. Stir well. Garnish with the lime wedge.'),
('2911870f-a3a9-47ad-a9e3-72e8ba0383bf', 'Foxy Lady', null, 'Cocktail glass', true, 'Shake all ingredients with ice, strain into a chilled cocktail glass, and serve.'),
('c3f66efe-7d5b-4da9-8258-40e58e419c6a', 'Godfather', null, 'Old-fashioned glass', true, 'Pour all ingredients directly into old fashioned glass filled with ice cubes. Stir gently.'),
